{"name": "pinecone-plugin-interface", "metadata": {"name": "pinecone-plugin-interface", "version": "0.0.7", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://www.pinecone.io", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": "https://pinecone.io/docs", "dependencies": [], "summary": "Plugin interface for the Pinecone python client", "upload_time": 1717552670}, "documentation": ["This small package is used to distribute a few classes and utilities used to build and consume plugins for the [Pinecone Python SDK](https://github.com/pinecone-io/pinecone-python-client).\n\nAt present this package is experimental and intended for internal use by Pinecone engineers iterating on new features. It should not be used by end-users or partners."], "modules": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.C", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.PluginMetadata", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.PluginMetadata.target_object", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["What SDK object are you trying to extend with a plugin? For initial use cases, this\nwill always be 'Pinecone', which refers to the Pinecone class in the python sdk."]}, {"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.PluginMetadata.namespace", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This is the attribute of the target object that will hold a reference to the \ninstantiated plugin implementation.\n\nFor example, you could have this plugin implementation:\n\n```\n# pinecone_plugin/my_plugin/__init__.py\nclass MyPlugin(PineconePlugin):\n    def __init__(self, client_builder, config):\n        pass\n\n    def feature(self):\n        return \"feature-response\"\n\n__installables__ = [PluginMetadata('Pinecone', 'foo', MyPlugin)]\n```\n\nAfter installation in the python sdk, this plugin would be accessible like so:\n\n```\nfrom pinecone import Pinecone\n\npc = Pinecone(api_key='key')\npc.foo.feature()  # returns 'feature-response'\n```"]}, {"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.PluginMetadata.implementation_class", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "PineconePlugin", "xref": {"fqname": "pinecone_plugin_interface.plugin_metadata.pinecone_plugin.PineconePlugin", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "C", "xref": {"fqname": "C", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["This should be a class extending the PineconePlugin abstract base class. This class should expose\nvarious feature methods with UX in mind, since it's the surface end-users will\ninteract with. Often it will be a wrapper around a generated OpenAPI client object."]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.pinecone_plugin", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.pinecone_plugin.C", "type": null, "documentation": ["Config type"]}, {"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.pinecone_plugin.T", "type": null, "documentation": ["openapi client instance"]}], "classes": [{"name": "pinecone_plugin_interface.pinecone_plugin.PineconePlugin", "bases": ["ABC"], "methods": [{"name"